org.springframework.beans.factory.support
Class ManagedMap

java.lang.Object
  org.springframework.beans.factory.support.ManagedMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Map
public class ManagedMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map

Tag subclass used to hold managed Map values, which may include runtime bean references.

Wraps a target Map, which will be a linked map if possible (that is, if running on JDK 1.4 or if Commons Collections 3.x is available).

Since:
27-May-2003
Author:
Juergen Hoeller
See Also:
CollectionFactory.createLinkedMapIfPossible(int)
